---
import MainLayout from '../../../layouts/MainLayout.astro';
import MotuSidebar from '../../../components/MotuSidebar.astro';
---

<MainLayout title="MOTU UltraLite mk3 — General Settings">
  <div class="flex gap-8 items-start">
    <div class="w-[250px] flex-shrink-0">
      <MotuSidebar />
    </div>
    <article class="prose prose-invert max-w-none">
      <h1>General Settings</h1>

      <h2>Front Panel LCD Navigation</h2>
      <p>The front-panel LCD and its rotary encoder provide access to all key settings without needing CueMix FX open on the computer. Navigation:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Turn the knob:</strong> cycles through parameters and changes values.</li>
        <li><strong>Press the knob:</strong> enters a submenu or confirms a selection.</li>
        <li><strong>Hold Select:</strong> accesses the top-level menu.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>Key LCD-accessible parameters: Input gains (all channels), Monitor output level, Headphone volume, Sample rate, Clock source, Phantom power (+48V) per channel.</p>

      <h2>Setting Clock and Sample Rate from the Front Panel</h2>
      <ol>
        <li>Hold <strong>Select</strong> to enter the main menu.</li>
        <li>Navigate to <strong>Clock Source</strong> — set to Internal for standard use.</li>
        <li>Navigate to <strong>Sample Rate</strong> — select 44.1 kHz for most sessions; 96 kHz for high-resolution Hydrasynth recording.</li>
        <li>Press the knob to confirm each setting.</li>
      </ol>

      <h2>Front Panel Lock</h2>
      <p>During a live performance session, accidental knob bumps can change gain or monitoring levels mid-show. To prevent this: <strong>hold Select for 3 seconds</strong> to lock the front panel. All physical controls are disabled until unlocked. The LCD shows a lock indicator. Repeat to unlock.</p>

      <h2>Phantom Power Management</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Enable +48V phantom power on inputs that require it (condenser microphones only).</li>
        <li><strong>The SM58 is a dynamic mic — leave phantom power OFF on Input 1 at all times.</strong> Hot-plugging a dynamic mic with phantom power active causes a loud transient thump through the monitoring chain.</li>
        <li>The Hydrasynth, VT-3, and P-225 connect as line-level sources — never enable phantom power on their input channels.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Firmware Updates</h2>
      <ol>
        <li>Download the latest firmware <code>.bin</code> file from <a href="https://motu.com/en-us/download/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">motu.com/download</a>.</li>
        <li>Open MOTU's firmware updater utility (included with the driver package).</li>
        <li>Follow the on-screen steps to flash the firmware to the UltraLite-mk3. Do not disconnect the unit during the update.</li>
        <li>After update completes: reboot the unit and re-open CueMix FX to verify the connection.</li>
      </ol>

      <h2>Driver Installation (Windows)</h2>
      <ol>
        <li>Download the latest ASIO driver from <a href="https://motu.com/en-us/download/#category=8&amp;product=235" target="_blank" rel="noopener">MOTU UltraLite-mk3 drivers page</a>.</li>
        <li>Run the installer and reboot when prompted.</li>
        <li>Connect the MOTU to a rear motherboard USB port (not a hub).</li>
        <li>Open Ableton → Preferences → Audio → Driver Type: ASIO → Audio Device: MOTU UltraLite-mk3.</li>
      </ol>
    </article>
  </div>
</MainLayout>